     <td valign=top width=470>                                                              


      <center>
      <table border=0 cellpadding=3 cellspacing=0 width=475>
	    <tr>
         <td style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 10pt;" background="/images/bg_heading_blue_01.jpg"><center><b>Concept for new guild, need input/suggestions</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
		 <td>                            
	                                   

	    <table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
		  <tr><td><font color="00dd00">Submitted by:</td><td><font color="00dd00">Ulfius</td></tr>
        </table>
	  <br>
	  <br>


          I would like to found a roleplaying guild that would be based off the model of the Knights Of Truth. The goal of the guild would NOT be helping one another to advance through levels or equipment or such (though brothers of the order would certainly help one another as needed), but ROLEPLAYING would be THE sole and primary goal of the order.<br>
          <br>
          The order would be based on the idea of a Medieval monastic/knightly brotherhood. Therefore the order would be NECESSARILY intolerant and bigoted (but NOT against RL races). It would ONLY admit good members, possibly only members who worship Mithaniel Marr, and most likely ONLY Paladins and Clerics. The order would bar entrance to all evil races/classes and even forbid members to consort with/aid/trade with them. We could even add other restrictions, such as forbidding the use of alcholol (in game), to make things more realistic.<br>
          <br>
          Furthermore, members of the order would be active proslytizers, travelling Norrath attempting to convince other players of the superiority of Mithaniel Marr. We could hold weekly services (in game), maybe even send missionaries to Neriak. <br>
          <br>
          So, restrictive and limiting as this is, WHY would I want to create such a guild? In a word: ROLEPLAYING. It would greatly enhance the ambiance of the game and help players contribute as a part of the theatrical landscape. However, I would ONLY consider making such a guild if I could get enough people really interested in making it happen. So that's why I put this call out, to see if anyone else out there shares that interest.<br>
          <br>
          Please email me at myke@tidalwave.net and let me know.<br>
          </td>
		 </tr>
		</table>

		
		
